rdf:Description.dct:title: application
rdf:Description.dct:description: This register contains the sub-types of the media type "application" used for spatial data sets in INSPIRE, in particular in INSPIRE download services. Whenever sub-types exist that are registered with IANA or are in the registration process these are used. For all other formats, no commonly used sub-type exists and INSPIRE has to - at least temporarily - define their own types. In accordance with the rules for media types in RFC 2046/RFC 4288, these start with "x-". At this time, all entries in this register have the status 'valid'. Sub-types that are no longer recommended for use will be marked as 'deprecated', but will always be kept in this register as download services may still be using deprecated sub-types.

rdf:Description.dct:title: x-shapefile
rdf:Description.dct:description: The media type shall be used for Esri shapefiles. The file is a zip archive that contains at least the shp, shx and dbf files.

rdf:Description.dct:title: x-filegdb
rdf:Description.dct:description: The media type shall be used for Esri file geodatabases. The file is a zip archive that contains the gdb directory.

rdf:Description.dct:title: x-gmz
rdf:Description.dct:description: The media type shall be used for a zip archive that contains one or more GML documents.

rdf:Description.dct:title: x-ecw
rdf:Description.dct:description: The media type shall be used for Enhanced Compressed Wavelet (ECW) files.

rdf:Description.dct:title: x-ascii-grid
rdf:Description.dct:description: The media type shall be used for ASCII GRID files.

rdf:Description.dct:title: x-oracledump
rdf:Description.dct:description: The media type shall be used for Oracle dumps. This media type is incomplete as it misses a reference to the specification of the format.

rdf:Description.dct:title: x-las
rdf:Description.dct:description: The media type shall be used for the LASer file format (LAS).

rdf:Description.dct:title: x-laz
rdf:Description.dct:description: The media type shall be used for compressed LAS files. This media type is incomplete as it misses a reference to the specification of the format.

rdf:Description.dct:title: x-tab
rdf:Description.dct:description: The media type shall be used for the MapInfo TAB format. The file is a zip archive that contains at least the tab, dat, map and id files.

rdf:Description.dct:title: x-tab-raster
rdf:Description.dct:description: The media type shall be used for the MapInfo Raster TAB format. This media type is incomplete as it misses a reference to the specification of the format.

rdf:Description.dct:title: x-worldfile
rdf:Description.dct:description: The media type shall be used for world files. The file extension usually depends on the format of the associated image, e.g. .jgw for JPEG (2000) oder .tfw for TIFF.
